						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar left of the entrance to the Vālīśvara temple. . • • .</p>						

						<p>Undated. Palaeographically datable to 16th-17th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>Seems to refer to a levy of grain on the lands irrigated by the tank of Lēbūru. (<hi rend="italic">Inscriptions of the Nellore District,</hi> Part II, p. 810, No. 43).</p>						

